  <section class="section-pad" style="background:var(--white);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="copy-grid">
        <div class="copy-block">
          <h2>Boiler Servicing in Liverpool's Older Properties</h2>
          <h3 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin:0.75rem 0 0.4rem;text-align:center;">Do older Liverpool boilers need servicing more often?</h3>
          <p>Not necessarily more often, but the consequences of missing a service are greater. Liverpool's older housing stock frequently contains boilers that are 10 to 20 years old. These boilers are more prone to scale build-up, seal deterioration and ignition problems. Annual servicing is the only reliable way to catch deteriorating components before they cause a breakdown. The <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/domestic/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HSE recommends annual servicing</a> for all domestic gas appliances regardless of age.</p>
          <h3 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin:0.75rem 0 0.4rem;text-align:center;">Is a boiler service the same as a boiler repair?</h3>
          <p>No. A service is a planned maintenance visit to check, clean and optimise the boiler. A repair is reactive work to fix a fault that has already developed. Regular servicing significantly reduces the likelihood of needing a repair. If our engineer identifies a fault during the service, they explain it clearly and provide a written quote before carrying out any additional work. See <a href="https://energysavingtrust.org.uk/advice/boilers/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Energy Saving Trust boiler servicing guidance</a> for independent advice.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="copy-block">
          <h2>Boiler Servicing for Liverpool Landlords and Letting Agents</h2>
          <h3 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin:0.75rem 0 0.4rem;text-align:center;">Are landlords legally required to service boilers?</h3>
          <p>The annual legal requirement for landlords is the gas safety certificate (CP12), not specifically a boiler service. However, boiler manufacturers require annual servicing to maintain warranty cover, and the <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/landlords/index.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HSE</a> requires landlords to keep all gas appliances in good working order. In practice this means an annual service is essential. We recommend combining both in a single visit for £120. <a href="https://liverpool.gov.uk/housing/landlords/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Liverpool City Council</a> actively inspects rental properties and a well-serviced boiler protects against enforcement action.</p>
          <h3 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin:0.75rem 0 0.4rem;text-align:center;">Can a letting agent book a boiler service on behalf of a landlord?</h3>
          <p>Yes. We work with Liverpool letting agents directly, coordinating access with tenants and providing all certificates and documentation to the agent and landlord. If you are a letting agent managing multiple Liverpool properties, call us to discuss a preferred supplier arrangement. See <a href="https://www.nrla.org.uk/resources/gas-safety" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NRLA guidance on landlord gas obligations</a> for further information on landlord responsibilities.</p>
